			<outline text="January 3" type="calendarDay" name="03" >
				<outline text="We love our &quot;no hugging and no learning,&quot; &quot;nobody grows, nothing changes&quot; situation comedies, but should we? &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/KnRS43yK0I&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 03 Jan 2022 15:48:37 GMT" tweetId="1478030546475356162" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1478030546475356162" inReplyToId="" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
				<outline text="&quot;. . . a situation that is as much social as it is medical. Covid-19 is a medical condition, but a pandemic is a social and political phenomenon, and shame on any government that doesn’t treat it as such.&quot; --Tim Dunlop &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/bLPSAaw5de&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 03 Jan 2022 12:29:14 GMT" tweetId="1477980370889023489" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1477980370889023489" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
				<outline text="Sadly, a sentence reusable in various contexts.

“No self-governing society can survive such a threat by denying that it exists.” &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/jvPLNO3hau&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Mon, 03 Jan 2022 11:53:31 GMT" tweetId="1477971380381573121" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1477971380381573121" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
