			<outline text="January 1" type="calendarDay" name="01" >
				<outline text="Stock lingo for cop-outs. In Don't Look Up, one quiet touch is the use of always-at-hand stock language to excuse the inexcusable. &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/0DRry8i8zo&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sun, 02 Jan 2022 03:55:34 GMT" tweetId="1477488714892955648" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1477488714892955648" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
				<outline text="...made me think that a marginalized people are in thrall not just to economics and legal structures, but also to attitudes, including attitudes of entitlement held by the powerful, all of which define those people, their place, the limits of their power and public speech. &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/eiAJuMmtLy&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Sat, 01 Jan 2022 14:59:58 GMT" tweetId="1477293527847559169" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1477293527847559169" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
